latestIgtvVideos.title: Creating A Safe Space
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
DYK that October 11th is #NationalComingOutDay? 

Coming out is one of the most difficult things you will ever do. Finding a safe space that is full of love and support and free of judgement is vital, and, the most incredible feeling. In an effort to help create a safe space for everyone right here on my Instagram account I am sharing my coming out story in partnership with @nyxcosmetics_canada and @itgetsbettercanada.

 I encourage those of you who have a story to tell to share it in the comments below, tag your gay BFF, and let's create a community in the comments that allows those out there who may need the inspiration and courage to feel loved and understood. I can't wait to hear YOUR stories. 

 #DoTheDaniel #ItGetsBetterProject #ad

latestIgtvVideos.title: Kicking off #Pride2020
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Today officially marks the beginning of #PrideMonth and I am feeling a lot of things this year. I will be very privileged to share positive messages of hope and unity. Like this one from a #Pride Campaign with @mercedesbenzcanada last year. I will be sharing ways that we as a #LGBTQ community can come together digitally to celebrate and have our voices heard.

But let us never forget my friends, that our voices are heard today because of our own riots and fires. I look forward to celebrating #Pride with you all and helping to share things here and on the blog, and offering my platform for as a safe space we can all come together.

latestPosts.caption:
If I told you that there was a destination that offered some of the best food in the world, the biggest & best festivals, the most beautiful sights and sounds in nature, and one of the most fabulous celebrations of the year that I NEVER miss, would you be surprised if I said it was right here in Canada? 

I'm here to tell you that all of this, and so much more awaits YOU in @tourismequebec this summer! Whether you've recently visited in the colder months for those winter moments we all know and love, or it's been years since your last vacation in Québec, this is your reminder that the sights, sounds, people, and tastes of one of Canada's most beautiful provinces are even better than you remember! This summer, why not embrace a whole new side of Québec that you didn't realize was waiting for you? 

I'd LOVE to know what your favourite destination or summer experience is in Québec? Maybe even tag your favourite small businesses too and let's celebrate everything that it means to say Bonjour Québec in the beauty of the summer months!  

Curious to learn more? Head to the link in my bio and join me in saying #BonjourQuebec this summer in the best ways possible!

#ad #Quebec #SupportLocal #LocalTravel #ExploreCanada #DoTheDaniel #DanielReyesCocka

I recently had the pleasure of attending Pride in Motion in one of my favourite @reebokcanada head to toe looks. 💅🏻

The event was an immersive, scent-led movement experience hosted by @wearejaybird in collaboration with @_vigyl, a queer-led Canadian fragrance house.

At the centre of the experience was Hanlan’s — VIGYL’s cult-favourite candle inspired by Toronto’s iconic queer landmark, Hanlan’s Point.

As part of Pride Month celebrations, $10 from every Hanlan’s candle sold in June will be donated directly to the @rainbowrailroad 🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍⚧️✨

I'm OBSESSED with the scent and you can get yours today to support not only this incredible queer owned business, but also the very important work Rainbow Railroad does by heading to www.vigyl.ca 🕯️

Happy Pride everyone 🤍🩷🩵❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🤎🖤

#VIGYL #Jaybird #Hanlans #Pride #AllInPrideToronto #PrideToronto #PrideMonth #Queer #Gay #LGBT #2SLGBTQIA #DoTheDaniel #DanielReyesCocka

This is your sign that you NEED to visit @tourismlondon and the ALL NEW @hrhlondonontario this summer 🌞⛱️ 

Located at @100kellogg, this spectacular hotel allows you to channel your inner rockstar in all the right ways.

From the three distinct restaurants for the best food, to the curated tours available daily to both guests and non guests of the hotel featuring memorabilia from some of the best Canadian artists and musicians, this is a hotel experience that you will never forget! 

Being attached to #100KelloggLane also allows you the opportunity to immerse yourself in one of a kind experiences like @factoryldnont, @theclubhouseldn, @beer.kitchen & @londonchildrensmuseum.

And in case you're wondering, my fabulous outfit at the end of this video was to celebrate the upcoming launch of High Tea at the hotel coming later this month and just in time for Pride Celebrations 🏳️‍🌈🎉🫖

So... Are YOU ready to live like a rockstar this summer at #HardRockHotelLondon?🤘🏻🎸🔥

latestPosts.caption:
ICYMI I was recently invited by @mazdacanada & @coffeeassoccanada to experience The 2025 #MazdaCoffeeTour and it was one of my favourite days  in a long time! 

Curated to showcase the vibrant coffee scene, we got behind the wheel of #MazdaCX70 and #MazdaCX90 vehicles and explored six unique cafe's, coffee shops, and espresso bars. Each of them offered something to learn, try, experience, drink and eat. And to my surprise, asides from our first stop (all six listed below) I had never been to them before.

📍 @balzacscoffee in @distilleryto - 52 Distillery Lane
📍 @sbtxt.coffee in @torontojunction - 130 Cawthra Avenue 
📍 @gateau_ghost in @tolittleitaly - 974 College Street 
📍 @tsuchi.cafe in @tolittleitaly - 688 College Street 
📍@piccolo__caffe - 111 John Street 
📍 @cafereneebar - 100 Portland Street

I was invited to end the day at @1hotel.toronto and it was the most magical way to end such an amazing day.

I LOVE how many new friends I made that day! Thank you again #MazdaCanada and #CoffeeAssociationOfCanada for inviting me to join in with you 💓☕🍵

#SeeTorontoNow #Toronto #TorontoRestaurants #Coffee #Cafe #SupportLocal #ShopLocal #DoTheDaniel #DanielReyesCocka

After careful consideration, we've decided to make some last minute changes to the bench this season. Effective immediately, we have made the difficult choice to part ways with the following personalities this Pride Month 🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍⚧️✨

Crash out Courtney, Lash out Leanna and Burnout Bonnie are no longer with the company. 

Similarly, after receiving her probation review from her manager, we also will not be offering Divorce-as-her-entire-personality Debbie a permanent position  with the organization. 

We'd like to say thank you to these ladies for their time as part of the team, and we wish them well in their future endeavors. 🤭

Because (all jokes aside) I have come to learn babes, that you gotta put down the personalities that feel the most comfortable in order to heal, move on, and be happy. Can't open new doors with old keys.
